<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-09-0240 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author compares the 1986 Defense budget with the one approved for1981. He concludes that the greatest percentage increases have been U.S.airlift-sealift forces, strategic forces, and intelligence and communicationsoperations. He recommends some steps that can be taken to reduce thebudget. He also looks at how the defense of NATO increases the budgetand gives some guidelines that need to be accepted by military and politicalleaders to realign the NATO divisions of responsibility. These shiftsin NATO defense strategy could eventually reduce the U.S. defense budget,he says.</TEXT></DOC>